task.summary: Default task
Added a README.md to the project
Added a README.md to the project
Merge remote-tracking branch 'origin/master'
Added example code to the project
Fixed TODOs in README.md
Added branches to the README.md
Added FunctionsToAdd.md
Added admin users, that can ask for data from the server - it is now possible to send data to the server - There is no logging at this point in time
Added admin users, that can ask for data from the server - it is now possible to send data to the server - There is no logging at this point in time
Added the possibility to send data to the webpage - It does not send the correct data - Sends place holder data now - Started a draft of how the data can be stored in firebase
Added the possibility to send data to the webpage - It does not send the correct data - Sends place holder data now - Started a draft of how the data can be stored in firebase
Started on exporting of data to a JSON database - Can read the json file - Can not write to the file yet - Added more text to multiple READMEs
Can now store sensor data in a local JSON database. - added a server-config.json, not used yet.
It is now possible to ask the server for data for a sensor or a controlled item
Added sensor-config.json to store the configuration for the sensors -Contains to example sensors
Added robot-config.json to store the configuration for the robots/units -Contains two example robots
Robots can now be authenticated and joins the correct room with the correct passcode - There is no functionality for the authenticated clients
Added some TODOs
renamed script.js to index.js
Changed package.json
moved some files
The passcode used by the robot can now be reused after the robot has disconnected
Fixed bug in printing of data received from robot - Prints now the datatype, time and value
The server now sends the setpoints to the robot when it is given the robot id. - There is no automatic sending of setpoint when it is changed.
The server now stores the robot id and passcode in the same object to simplify the structure.
JSClient.js can now send info of the controlled item based on whether the sensor value is over (true) or below (false). - Changed a typo in index.js, so it can now receive controlled item data
